title._content: Exhibit of space suits designed for Soviet Cosmonauts during ASTP

description._content: Collection: NASA Johnson Space Center Collection Title: Exhibit of space suits designed for Soviet Cosmonauts during ASTP Description: An exhibit illustrating the space suits designed for the Soviet Cosmonaut crewmen of the joint U.S.-U.S.S.R. Apollo Soyuz Test Project (ASTP) docking in Earth orbit mission. These were on display in the training building at the Cosmonaut Training Center (Star City) near Moscow.
